bd79b9c8-7857-4207-9f28-1c3f489a8315.05f348d4-d689-45f4-a337-aac1583b283c.description=Description\:
 
 This step adds a new entry in the /etc/oratab files on each node of a RAC cluster or on the local machine.

Note\: If Oracle version is higher than 11.2 and CRS Home exists, the whole Add Oratab entry functionality is skipped as Oracle will automatically add the necessary entry to ORATAB file.

Dependencies\: Step must run as the instance call wrapper.

Return codes\:
 0 \= step was successful
 any other value \= at least one ssh connection error occurred

Inputs\:
 command - executes Addoratabentry.py
 Cluster Nodes - Optional\: Comma-separated list of nodes where this database will run. Leave blank for non-clustered environments.
 CRS Home - Optional\: The location of the ORA_CRS_HOME where the database listener will be provisioned.
 Database Name - Required\: The name of the database.
 Instance Wrapper - Required\: The shell to run this step. This may include changing the user with the su or sudo commands.
 Oracle Home - Required\: The location of the ORACLE_HOME where the database resides.
 Oracle Version - Optional\: Version of the Oracle Home
 Start on Boot - Optional\: Should the database instance be started upon boot? (Y or N). This optional parameter only applies to database version pre 11gR2.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Instance Info - A comma-separated list of InstanceName\:ServerName.
 Oracle SID - The Oracle Server (Instance) ID.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 This step gathers and validates the optional advanced parameters for the Provision an Oracle Database workflow.

 Dependencies\: None

 Return code\:

 Otherwise, the step returns a 1.

 DBCA Password SYS - No description
 DBCA Password SYSMAN - No description
 DBCA Password SYSTEM - No description
 DBCA Response File - Optional\: Location of a DBCA response file in the software repository to download. If not specified, a default will be used.
 DBCA Template File - Optional\: DBCA template file or template name. If template not found in Oracle default location or system temporary location it will be downloaded from software repository. If not specified, a default will be General_Purpose.dbc.
 Inventory Files - Optional\: Comma-separated list of fully-qualified Oracle inventory files. If this parameter is not specified, the workflow looks for the oraInst.loc file in /etc and /var/opt/oracle.

(R- Remote Location, 
L- Local Location,
<Location>\: destination path, 
<state> \: ‘alternate | reset | defer | enable’)

 Maximum Dump File Size - Optional\: maximum dump file size in K, M or G , Ex\: 200M. By default value will be set to 'unlimited'.
 NetCA Response File - Optional\: Location of a NetCA response file in the software repository to download. If not specified, a default will be used.
 Policy Managed - Optional\: Set to true if Database is policy managed and set to false if Database is admin managed. The default is false.
 RAC One Node - Optional\: Set to true to provision an Oracle RAC One Node database. The default is false.
 RAC One Node Service Name - Optional\: The name of the service to connect to the RAC One Node Database.
 Redo Log Destinations - Optional\: comma separated locations accessible by oracle user for Redo Log Mirroring.
 Variables File - Optional\: Location of a DBCA variables file in the software repository to download. If not specified, a default will be used.

 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

This step prepares instance level Oracle access.
 

Dependencies\:

Inputs\:
 command - executes PrepareOracleInstance.py

Results\:

 CRS Home - The last ORA_CRS_HOME location in the inventory file.

 bd79b9c8-7857-4207-9f28-1c3f489a8315.4962cbb2-1dc7-4783-981a-4d9716b054ad.description=Description\:
 
 This step creates or verifies a NetCA response file. If the response file does not exist, it is created.
 
 Dependencies\: Step must run as the instance call wrapper.
 
 Return code\:
 
 Upon success and the port is not in use, the step returns a 0.
 Otherwise, the step returns a 1.

Inputs\:
 command - executes VerifyNetCAResponsev2.py
 Database Name - Required\: The name of the database to provision.
 Listener Name - Required\: The name the Oracle listener to use for this database.
 Listener Port - Required\: The port the Oracle listener is using (or should use) for this database.
 NetCA Home - Required\: The location of the ORACLE_HOME where the database listener will be provisioned.
 NetCA Response File - Required\: Location of a NetCA response file. If not specified, a default will be created.
 NetCA Wrapper - Required\: The jython call wrapper required to run as the user to run NetCA.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 NetCA Response File - Location of a NetCA response file.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
 bd79b9c8-7857-4207-9f28-1c3f489a8315.554a5651-89ae-44bc-94fd-f942f5324389.description=Description\:
 
 This step runs the catcpu or catpsu script depending on the latest CPU or PSU installed.
 
 Dependencies\: Step must run as the instance call wrapper.
 
 Return Codes\:
 0 \= Ran normally for a single server (non RAC) database.
 1 \= Error finding desired scripts.
 2 \= Ran normally for a RAC database.
 3 \= Ran normally, but unable to find the January 08 view recompile script.

Inputs\:
 command - executes RunLatestcpuorpsuScript.py
 Instance Info - Required\: A comma-separated list of InstanceName\:ServerName.
 Instance Wrapper - Required\: The shell to run this step. This may include changing the user with the su or sudo commands.
 Oracle Home - Required\: The fully-qualified name of the ORACLE_HOME for this instance.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Update Script - Name of the script found to update the database.
 View Script - Fully-qualified pathname of the script to recompile views.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 bd79b9c8-7857-4207-9f28-1c3f489a8315.5e8ca62f-1c99-4d18-b9ac-fc52e87e2e0a.description=Description\:

This step verifies the following\:

- The listener is already created.
- The Oracle version is 11.2.0.1 or above.

Note\: If CRS is already set up (the listener is already created), subsequent steps that run netca will not be executed.

Dependencies\: Step must be run as the instance call wrapper.

Return code\:
0 \= The listener already exists
1 \= At least one error occurred in this step
2 \= The listener does not already exist

Inputs\:
 command - executes VerifyListenerv2.py
 CRS Home - Required\: The last ORA_CRS_HOME location in the inventory file.
 Instance Wrapper - Required\: The jython call wrapper required to run as the oracle user.
 Local Listener - Optional\: If True than the verify listener step will ignore any GRID installation listener and attempt to create a local listener. If environment does not include GRID than local listener will be created regardless of this setting. Default value is False.
 Oracle Home - Required\: The RDBMS Oracle Home.
 Oracle Version - Required\: Version of the installed Oracle.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 bd79b9c8-7857-4207-9f28-1c3f489a8315.description=<pre>
 Purpose

This workflow provisions an Oracle database on an Oracle Standalone, Grid Standalone, or CRS RAC environment.

 Description

This workflow creates a new Oracle database using the Oracle supplied DBCA utility.

The supplied DBCA template has the information on file layout and init.ora parameters.

If using ASM, the file layout is ignored and all files are positioned on the specified _Datafile Location_ except for the online logs and control files.

The version of the software is determined using sqlplus. The sqlplus version is only used to determine the ORACLE_HOME of the listener. For Oracle RAC 11.2, the listener must run from the ASM/CRS home. In all other cases the listener is created from the database ORACLE_HOME.



 Dependencies

The ORACLE_HOME has already been installed and is ready for the DBCA to run.

 Usage Instructions

Review the input parameters listed below, and create a deployment using values appropriate for your environment. The workflow should be run following the Provision Oracle Software workflow.

 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 Database Name - Required\: The name of the database to provision.
 Database.Name - No description
 Datafile Location - Required\: Database file locations. For example\: /u01/app/oracle/oradata or +DATA (ASM)
 Instance.name - No description
 Oracle Base - Required\: The location of the Oracle Base of the Oracle install. This is where the admin directory is located.
 Server.Become Routine - No description

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 NetCA Response File - Optional\: Location of a NetCA response file in the software repository to download. If not specified, a default will be used.
 DBCA National Character Set - No description
 RAC One Node - Optional\: Set to true to provision an Oracle RAC One Node database. The default is false.
 Cleanup On Success - No description
 RAC One Node Service Name - Optional\: The name of the service to connect to the RAC One Node Database.
 ASM Password - Optional (required when provisioning an Oracle database using ASM storage)\: The password used to manage ASM.
 DBCA Password SYS - No description
 Log Archive Format - Optional\: string specifying archive log format. may contain %s | %S, %t | %T, %a, %d, %r variables. Ex\: 'arch_%t_%s_%r.arc' , %t_%s_%r.dbf
 Archivelog ON - Optional\: set to True to provision database in ARCHIVELOG mode. By default value is set to False
 Oracle Account - Optional (required only if inventory does not exist)\: Oracle user that will own the Oracle Home.
 Cleanup On Failure - No description
 Variables File - Optional\: Location of a DBCA variables file in the software repository to download. If not specified, a default will be used.
 DBCA Response File - Optional\: Location of a DBCA response file in the software repository to download. If not specified, a default will be used.
 DBCA Password SYSMAN - No description
 DBCA Character Set - No description
 Log Archive Destination - Optional\: comma separated values specifying archive log destinations in the format ‘\: \: ’
(R- Remote Location, 
L- Local Location,
\: destination path, 
 \: ‘alternate | reset | defer | enable’)
 Listener Configuration - Optional\: Colon-separated name and port of the Oracle listener for this database. If left blank, the Oracle default of LISTENER\:1521 will be used.
 DBCA Template File - Optional\: DBCA template file or template name. If template not found in Oracle default location or system temporary location it will be downloaded from software repository. If not specified, a default will be General_Purpose.dbc.
 DBCA Password ALL - Optional\: If set, this password will be used in the DBCA response file for the oracle.install.db.config.starterdb.password.ALL setting and the remaining DBCA Password inputs will be ignored.
 Local Listener - Optional\: If True than the verify listener step will ignore any GRID installation listener and attempt to create a local listener. If environment does not include GRID than local listener will be created regardless of this setting. Default value is False.
 Maximum Dump File Size - Optional\: maximum dump file size in K, M or G , Ex\: 200M. By default value will be set to 'unlimited'.
 Policy Managed - Optional\: Set to true if Database is policy managed and set to false if Database is admin managed. The default is false.
 DBCA Password SYSTEM - No description
 Redo Log Destinations - Optional\: comma separated locations accessible by oracle user for Redo Log Mirroring.
 Inventory Files - Optional\: Comma-separated list of fully-qualified Oracle inventory files. If this parameter is not specified, the workflow looks for the oraInst.loc file in /etc and /var/opt/oracle.
 DBCA Password DBSNMP - No description
 Cluster Nodes - Optional\: List of nodes where this database will run. Required when provisioning a RAC database. Leave blank for non-clustered environments.
 Oracle Home - Optional\: The ORACLE_HOME to use if more than one Oracle Home exists in the inventory file(s).
 Container Database - Optional\: Set to 'True' if provisioning a container database in Oracle 12c, set to 'False' otherwise. Default is 'False'.

 Results Verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. The Output tab will indicate whether the database creation was successful. 

To further verify the results\:

\# Log in to the target server.
\# Set the ORACLE_HOME and ORACLE_SID.
\# Log in using command\: sqlplus / as sysdba 
\# Run the command\: select name from v$database;
\# If you see your database name listed then the database has been provisioned and is online.




 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the OTHER FILES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
